      background — Android tints non-transparent pixels using the
      notification accent color, so multiple-color icons don't render.

      Shield silhouette (filled white) with `#` glyph cut out using even-odd
      fill rule, so the # reads as a visible cut against the white shield
      regardless of system tint.
    -->
